This problem should have been fixed on the 13th (bug 61949).  Builds before the 
14th would have an NPE on line 87:

	86:	IBundleGroup bundleGroup = getBundleGroup(featureId);
	87:	info.featurePluginLabel = bundleGroup.getName();

Since #getBundleGroup might return null.  However, it doesn't make sense that we 
would see on on line 87 in newer builds:

	77:	IProduct product = Platform.getProduct();
	78:	IBundleGroup bundleGroup = getBundleGroup(featureId);
	79:	if (product == null || bundleGroup == null)
	80:	    return null;
	81:
	82:	AboutInfo info = new AboutInfo(featureId);
	83:	info.versionId = versionId;
	84:
	85:	info.appName = ProductProperties.getAppName(product);
	86:	info.aboutText = ProductProperties.getAboutText(product);
	87:	info.aboutImage = ProductProperties.getAboutImage(product);
	88:	info.windowImages = ProductProperties.getWindowImages(product);

Since there is nothing on that line that wasn't read on previous lines.  Also, 
the value in question has already been checked against null (line 79).

Is it possible you were using an older load?
